gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Grizzlies 115, 76ers 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Grizzlies defeated the 76ers, 115-109. Jaren Jackson Jr. led the way for the Grizzlies with 30 points, 11 rebounds and six blocks, while Jake LaRavia added 19 points and a career-high 13 rebounds in the victory. Kelly Oubre Jr. tallied 25 points and four rebounds for the 76ers in the losing effort. The Grizzlies have won back-to-back games as they improve to 22-41 on the season, while the 76ers fall to 35-27.
